fields.value: Replication Data for: Balancing Disproportionality and Parliament Fragmentation: A Simulation Study of the Effect of District Magnitude on Electoral Outcomes

dsDescriptionValue.value: This dataset was created to allow replication code and data to be accessible to reviewers during double-blind review of the manuscript entitled: "Balancing Disproportionality and Parliament Fragmentation: A Simulation Study of the Effect of District Magnitude on Electoral Outcomes".

files.description: Data on PR election results in eight Western European countries (for the lower house) at a constituency level (1991-2016). Retrieved from: Kollman, Ken, Allen Hicken, Daniele Caramani, David Backer, and David Lublin. 2016. Constituency-Level Elections Archive. Produced and distributed by Ann Arbor, MI: Center for Political Studies, University of Michigan. This data can be used to plot an empirical distribution of vote proportions (proportional reprezentation elections) at a constituency level.
